4253,0.00824969,0.03416654,0.05756738,0.05657198,0.00269049,0.03161659,0.04469062,-0.01157313,0.04223869,0.10844916,0.04979218,0.04507628,-0.05510406,0.03341822,0.04820909,-0.00960459,-0.02308850,-0.05124604,0.02455556,-0.03354163,0.02292226,0.05769915,-0.03577389,0.02877164,0.00147295,-0.04161281,-0.00761458,-0.00383714,-0.05875509,0.02224370,-0.01465371,0.03614362,0.02235244,0.01380638,0.03539046,-0.03184317,0.02889481,0.03329775,0.03598692,0.01917508,0.01350364,0.01010975]',E'ActiveModel: nested persistence made simple\n\nPersist an entire object graph: user, profile (1-1), posts (1-N), and tags (M-N)\nin a single operation using a fluent builder API. SeaORM automatically determines\nthe dependencies and inserts or deletes objects in the correct order.\nThis requires the SeaORM 2.0 dense entity format.\n\n```rust\n// this creates the nested object as shown above:\nlet user = user::ActiveModel::builder()\n    .set_name("Bob")\n    .set_email("bob@sea-ql.org")\n    .set_profile(profile::ActiveModel::builder().set_picture("image.jpg"))\n    .add_post(\n        post::ActiveModel::builder()\n            .set_title("Nice weather")\n            .add_tag(tag::ActiveModel::builder().set_tag("sunny")),\n    )\n    .save(db)\n    .await?;\n```','{"source": "sea-orm", "version": "1.0", "language": "rust", "title": "\ud83d\udc1a SeaORM", "section_title": "README", "url": "https://github.com/SeaQL/sea-orm/blob/master/README.md", "topics": "seaorm,rust,orm,async,README", "categories": "database,orm,rust,async"}');
